}
```

### Integrating the `Operation` Interface in Tests

These implementations allow you to encapsulate the action and target item into an object that can be passed around, queued, or executed in a multithreaded environment. You'll instantiate specific `Operation` objects (like `InsertOperation`, `RemoveOperation`, or `ContainsOperation`) when building test workloads or when dynamically selecting operations to perform on the `RefinableHashSet`.

This design not only aligns with solid principles by separating the concerns but also enhances the testability and flexibility of your concurrent data structure testing framework.
